After a tedious and troublesome navigation of seventy seven days , this religious squadron cast anchor before Venice and their reception proclaimed the joy and magnificence of that powerful republic . 
In the command of the world , the modest Augustus had never claimed such honors from his subjects as were paid to his feeble successor by an independent state . 
Seated on the poop on a lofty throne , he received the visit , or , in the Greek style , the adoration of the doge and senators . 
They sighed to behold the spoils and trophies with which it had been decorated after the sack of Constantinople . 
