Four principal questions had been agitated between the two churches . 
The use of unleaven bread in the communion of Christ's body . 
The supremacy of the pope . 
The single or double procession of the Holy Ghost . 
In earthly affairs , it is not easy to conceive how an assembly equal of legislators can bind their successors invested with powers equal to their own . 
But the dictates of inspiration must be true and unchangeable nor should a private bishop , or a provincial synod , have presumed to innovate against the judgment of the Catholic church . 
Of this at least we may be sure , that neither side could be convinced by the arguments of their opponents . 
Prejudice may be enlightened by reason , and a superficial glance may be rectified by a clear and more perfect view of an object adapted to our faculties . 
