The prize which eluded the efforts of Petrarch , was obtained by the fortune and industry of his friend Boccace , the father of the Tuscan prose . 
In his passage , Petrarch entertained him at Padua a short time he enjoyed the scholar , but was justly offended with the gloomy and unsocial temper of the man . 
Discontented with the world and with himself , Leo depreciated his present enjoyments , while absent persons and objects were dear to his imagination . 
