Yet the fleeting shadows of metaphysics were pursued with more curiosity and ardor . 
After a long oblivion , Plato was revived in Italy by a venerable Greek , who taught in the house of Cosmo of Medicis . 
George Gemistus Pletho , a various and voluminous writer , the master of Bessarion , and all the Platonists of the times . 
He visited Italy in his old age , and soon returned to end his days in Peloponnesus . 
