The respective merits of Rome and Constantinople are compared and celebrated by an eloquent Greek , the father of the Italian schools . 
Those gods , and those men , had long since vanished but to the eye of liberal enthusiasm , the majesty of ruin restored the image of her ancient prosperity . 
to the honor of the original , and parents are delighted to be renewed , and even excelled , by the superior merit of their children . 
Constantinople , says the orator , is situate on a commanding point , between Europe and Asia , between the Archipelago and the Euxine . 
The harbor , encompassed on all sides by the sea , and the continent , is the most secure and capacious in the world . 
A broad and rapid stream may be introduced into the ditches and the artificial island may be encompassed , like Athens , by land or water . 
Two strong and natural causes are alleged for the perfection of the model of new Rome . 
But the free idea of Constantinople was formed and executed by a single mind and the primitive model was improved by the obedient zeal of the subjects and successors of the first monarch . 
