In his good faith towards the garrison of Sfetigrade , he was a lesson and example to his son Mahomet . 
Resigning the sceptre to his son , he retired to the pleasant residence of Magnesia but he retired to the society of saints and hermits . 
But he was soon awakened from his dreams of enthusiasm by the Hungarian invasion and his obedient son was the foremost to urge the public danger and the wishes of the people . 
These pious occupations were again interrupted by the danger of the state . 
Age or disease , misfortune or caprice , have tempted several princes to descend from the throne and they have had leisure to repent of their irretrievable step . 
But Amurath alone , in the full liberty of choice , after the trial of empire and solitude , has repeated his preference of a private life . 
