In the apprehension of modern times , Petrarch is the Italian songster of Laura and love . 
But in the eyes of Petrarch , and those of his graver contemporaries , his love was a sin , and Italian verse a frivolous amusement . 
From his earliest youth , Petrarch aspired to the poetic crown . 
In the preface to his first volume , he enumerates and weighs twenty Italian biographers , who have professedly treated of the same subject . 
It was , in truth , the retreat of a hermit and the moderns are much mistaken , if they place Laura and a happy lover in the grotto . 
