The ceremony of his coronation was performed in the Capitol , by his friend and patron the supreme magistrate of the republic . 
The grant was ratified by the authority of the senate and people and the character of citizen was the recompense of his affection for the Roman name . 
They did him honor , but they did him justice . 
The aspect of the seven hills and their majestic ruins confirmed these lively impressions and he loved a country by whose liberal spirit he had been crowned and adopted . 
Amidst the indulgence of enthusiasm and eloquence , Petrarch , Italy , and Europe , were astonished by a revolution which realized for a moment his most splendid visions . 
