But such voluntary obedience evaporates with the first transports of zeal and Rienzi felt the importance of justifying his usurpation by a regular form and a legal title . 
In this character , and with the consent of the Roman , the tribune enacted the most salutary laws for the restoration and maintenance of the good estate . 
By the first he fulfils the wish of honesty and inexperience , that no civil suit should be protracted beyond the term of fifteen days . 
But the execution of justice was hopeless till he had previously abolished the tyranny of the nobles . 
But these regulations would have been impotent and nugatory , had not the licentious nobles been awed by the sword of the civil power . 
