The dangerous office of tribune was successively occupied by two plebeians , Cerroni and Baroncelli . 
The mildness of Cerroni was unequal to the times and after a faint struggle , he retired with a fair reputation and a decent fortune to the comforts of rural life . 
Amidst the public misfortunes , the faults of Rienzi were forgotten and the Romans sighed for the peace and prosperity of their good estate . 
