His person was invisible , his name was yet formidable and the anxiety of the court of Avignon supposes , and even magnifies , his personal merit . 
Rienzi was indulged with an easy confinement and the use of books and in the assiduous study of Livy and the Bible , he sought the cause and the consolation of his misfortunes . 
