The long habits of obedience and education subdued the turbulent spirit of the nobles and commons of Rome . 
The barons forgot the arms and factions of their ancestors , and insensibly became the servants of luxury and government . 
The Colonna and Ursini vied with each other in the decoration of their palaces and chapels and their antique splendor was rivalled or surpassed by the sudden opulence of the papal families . 
In Rome the voice of freedom and discord is no longer heard and , instead of the foaming torrent , a smooth and stagnant lake reflects the image of idleness and servitude . 
