I am ignorant whether they have since continued in a progressive state . 
Yet Montfaucon still sighs for a more complete plan and description of the old city , which must be attained by the three following methods . 
The measurement of the space and intervals of the ruins . 
The study of inscriptions , and the places where they were found . 
The investigation of all the acts , charters , diaries of the middle ages , which name any spot or building of Rome . 
would furnish a solid and accurate basis for the ancient topography of Rome . 
The historian may applaud the importance and variety of his subject but while he is conscious of his own imperfections , he must often accuse the deficiency of his materials . 
